Edit: WOW this was almost a week late! My sincere apologies. I really like the conceit of this, and I think the addenda was very well done - the testing logs + diary entries in particular. It was unsettling in the way that made me get up and close my closet door before sitting back down to keep reading. However - I don't think the recipe part ties in well. I know it's the hand you were dealt, but themes like that need to tie in thematically as well as plot-wise, and the tenuous justification of  doesn't quite do it for me - the lake entity just doesn't seem congruent with that manner of trickery imo. I could be reading wrong, but that's my current feeling, so it's a no-vote from me.





